    <item>
      <title>Necromancers Trap (level 55 and 70 is a waste of time)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancerbalance&amp;message.id=3115#M3115</link>
      <description>The spell &amp;quot;Death Rune&amp;quot; ended going live as something far less than we would have prefered, being a last minute replacement for a spell we all liked very much (soul rune). As such it received very little testing or feedback. A quick browse of the necromancer forums will show comments such as &amp;quot;deleted from my spell book&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;totally worthless&amp;quot;. We were promised a review of the spells after they had gone live becasue they were placed in at the last minute and Id like to give some feedback now so that that can be done.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Firstly some facts about the trap, I will look at the level 70 version since I dont have the 55 :-&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;440 Damage per tick for 4 ticks (total 1760 damage) for 100 mana.&lt;br&gt;30 second recast timer.&lt;br&gt;6 seconds cast time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This makes it :-&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- 1st in terms of DPM!&lt;br&gt;- 7th most powerful dot in terms of DPS (73.3 DPS)&lt;br&gt;- 17th in terms of total damage!!!!!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Usability :&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Because it is non-targetable it is unusable in situations where crowd control is required.&lt;br&gt;- Because it despawns after 60 seconds it is often unusable in soloing situations (it can take several minutes to split mobs)&lt;br&gt;- Only one can be placed at a time (and even if we cold place more it wouldnt be possible with the 60 second timer and 30 seconds recast timer)&lt;br&gt;- Because of the 6 seconds cast time we cannot realistically drop or refresh the trap in the middle of a kite or fight while soloing.&lt;br&gt;- Im told we still get aggro from it - however the DPS is so low its a bit of a non issue.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bugs :&lt;br&gt;- Sometime kills itself.&lt;br&gt;- Sometimes causes the corpse to disappear on death.&lt;br&gt;- Sometimes disables all spell gems when cast.&lt;br&gt;- Sometimes will not trigger even if mob is dragged right over it!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So we have a dot which is unusable in most groups (due to CC, pulling ad placement issues) and because of the low total damage and long cast time we would be unlikely to mem for soloing.  Even though this has the highest DPM the damage is far more in line with a sub level 60 spell! In other words very few people are going to use it as part of their normal spell set up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now what I would do to adjust the problem I perceive with this spell (low DPS and total damage despite being highly situational) depends on how its supposed to be used.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If its supposed to be used only on pull AND be situational :-&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Triple the damage and quadrupple the mana cost.&lt;br&gt;While that would make it our number 1 dot in terms of DPS (220 DPS) and DPM, because it involves a mob being pulled right over it and thus a co-operative puller making only single pulls, it would still be situational. Id STILL expect not to be using this in most groups.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If its supposed to be used as part of our regular spell book :-&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Lower the cast time to 3.5 seconds.&lt;br&gt;- Double the damage and mana cost.&lt;br&gt;- Increase the despawn time to 5 minutes.&lt;br&gt;- Allow more than 1 to be in play at once.&lt;br&gt;- Ensure that they stack only if cast by different players.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thats what *I* would do, I know other will have different ideas.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In its current state though, &amp;quot;death rune&amp;quot; is a useless spell, and considering the time and effort put into programming for it, and the fact that we players expect to get spells from expansions that we will actually use; something SHOULD be done about it. Some feedback would be nice regarding what is being done.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alternatively, get rid of the trap altogether and give us back the soul rune aura *grin*&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Next Post : Mind Flay - the spell that is such a marginal upgrade that nobody even cares that they cant find it.&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
